reviewText: I have enjoyed the amazing Gaither's gospel music on television channels for many years and it is a great family tradition and worship. The voices of the Home Coming" group blend in so well that the music hall is filled with inspiration and love rendered in praising the lord. It is a music ministry of faith, hope, peace and harmony.Some of my favorite songs from this DVD are; "I've Just Seen Jesus" and "How Great Thou Art." This performance includes the works of George Beverly Shea, Sandi Patti and Larnelle Harris, Lynda Randle, and the gospel family of Bill and Gloria Gaither.1.Bill Gaither's 20 All-Time Favorite Homecoming Songs & Performances, Vol. 12.Bill & Gloria Gaither: Tent Revival Homecoming3.Gaither Homecoming Celebration!4.Bill Gaither Presents: Country Bluegrass Homecoming, Vol. 1

reviewText: Over the years Bill and Gloria Gaither have hosted and produced a series of videos featuring what has become a Christian family tradition, an assemblage of gospel artists and southern gospel groups. Although my wife have attended several Gaither concerts in years past and enjoyed their recorded music we have only recently began to enjoy the value of the Homecoming series for their entertainment, inspiration, and worship."20 All-Time Favorite Homecoming Songs Volume 2" is made up of many of our own favorite numbers from the many concerts we have now collected and enjoyed on tape.A few of our favorites include: How Great Thou Art, Leave it There, I've Just Seen Jesus, and When I Get to the End of the Way. The artists featured on these numbers, in the same order, are: George Beverly Shea, Homecoming Friends group, Sandi Patti and Larnelle Harris, and Lynda Randle.Classic Gaither Concert Style, beautifully narrated by Bill Gaither, reminiscent of an era of Gospel Music now being reproduced on CD's for another generation to enjoy.
